------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Requirements                                                         -
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Python version 2.6 or 2.7 (Not 3.x ready yet.)
    (Version 2.5 is missing the multiprocessing module.)

Python Packages:
argparse (if using python 2.6)
discover (if you want to run all the tests at once)
yaml

------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Setup                                                                -
------------------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Running                                                              -
------------------------------------------------------------------------
    To perform a simulation, create a new directory (probably in the
data directory) and place parameters and object graph configuration
files in that directory:

mkdir data/new_simulation
cp examples/parameters.yaml examples/object_graph.yaml data/new_simulation

    Goto that directory and run cli.py:

cd data/new_simulation
../../cli.py

    To analyze the data, stay in the same directory and use console.py:

../../console.py

    Once in the console, you can browse the HDF5 data file created by
the simulation, and use a wide variety of available tools.  Check the
actin_dynamics/analysis module for more info.

    To run a standard suite of measurements, just type:

analysis.perform_all(hdf_file)

